        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-lsvr-l3dl-09.txt</link>
        <title>"Layer-3 Discovery and Liveness", Randy Bush, Rob Austein, Keyur Patel</title>
        <dc:date>2022-05-02T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>In Massive Data Centers, BGP-SPF and similar routing protocols are used to build topology and reachability databases.  These protocols need to discover IP Layer-3 attributes of links, such as neighbor IP addressing, logical link IP encapsulation abilities, and link liveness.  This Layer-3 Discovery and Liveness protocol collects these data, which may then be disseminated using BGP-SPF and similar protocols.</description>
    </item>
